alert.note: Alert for Carver; Dakota; Hennepin; Scott (Minnesota) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Flood Warning issued May 24 at 8:49PM CDT until May 27 at 11:00AM CDT by NWS Minneapolis
info.description: ...The Flood Warning continues for the following river in Minnesota... Minnesota River at Savage affecting Scott, Hennepin, Dakota and Carver Counties. ...The Flood Warning is cancelled for the following river in Minnesota... Minnesota River near Jordan affecting Scott, Carver and Sibley Counties. ...FLOOD WARNING NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL LATE SATURDAY MORNING... * WHAT...Minor flooding is occurring and minor flooding is forecast. * WHERE...Minnesota River at Savage. * WHEN...Until late Saturday morning. * IMPACTS...At 705.0 feet, Flood waters begin to impact the park road at Fort Snelling State Park. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 700 PM CDT Wednesday, the stage was 704.3 feet. - Recent Activity...The maximum river stage in the 24 hours ending at 700 PM CDT Wednesday was 704.6 feet. - Forecast...The river is expected to fall below flood stage Friday afternoon and continue falling to 698.0 feet Wednesday evening. - Flood stage is 702.0 feet. - Flood History...This crest compares to a previous crest of 704.4 feet on 07/02/2013. &&
info.instruction: Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles.
